The ground state UV–Vis absorption spectra of (π)Pc-GQDs and (c)Pc-GQDs together with their component materials (Pc and GQDs) in DMSO are presented in Fig. 5
                        . GQDs were observed to have an absorption band at 350 nm associated with n- π∗ transitions of CO [18]. There were no significant shifts in the Q-bands (Table 1
                        ) of the spectra for the conjugate compared to the Pcs alone. Lack of signs of aggregation (splitting or broadening of Q-bands [28,29]) in the spectra confirmed that conjugation was between Pc and GQDs not between two Pcs, especially in (π)Pc-GQDs.
